    "The property of emergent capabilities in foundation models further complicates questions of accountability and the prevention of harmful outcomes, as unwanted, model behavior might arise unexpectedly (Bender et al. 2021; Bommasani et al. 2021).",
    "Consequentially, continuous monitoring and the implementation of fast-response safety protocols for worstcase scenarios become ever more critical in AI deployment, as organizational abilities to accurately foresee and prevent potential risks decrease.",
    "In the context of effective risk mitigation, some consider the homogenization of AI models and the centralization of computing capacities in the hands of a few commercial providers a regulatory opportunity: regulatory frameworks could leverage the central position of foundation model and infrastructure providers, for example through know-your-customer obligations, rather than posing a high regulatory burden on each deploying organization individually (Mo ¨kander et al. 2023).",
    "Lastly, the carbon emissions and energy consumption associated with the training and deployment of large-scale foundation models are gaining attention (Bender et al. 2021).",
    "Organizations hence need to consider ways to incorporate respective environmental impact into sustainability strategies and corporate responsibility efforts."
  ],
